Singer Mr Eazi, has reassured his fans that his next album will be worth the long wait. Known for pioneering ‘Banku’ music, a sound characterised by percolating rhythms and laid-back vocal delivered in Ghanaian Pidgin English, Mr Eazi explained the project is seemingly being ‘delayed’ because it promises to be special and different. The Ghana-based performer also noted details of the album will be made public in due time.   Instagram bans Kanye West for 24 hours     2022 AMVCA holds May 14     Lagos recognises actress Toyin Abraham   The music star in his reassuring post wrote: “I KNOW YOU GUYS ARE WAITING FOR THE ALBUM. KEEP WAITING, IT’S GONNA BE SPECIAL AND DIFFERENT!! AND WHEN IT’S READY, I WILL LET Y’ALL KNOW.” Born Oluwatosin Ajibade, the 30-year-old released his first body of work, “Life is Eazi, Vol. 1 – Accra to Lagos”, a 14-tracked album in 2017. His last body of work, an EP (Extended Play) titled, “Something Else” consisting of 5 tracks was released in 2021.